<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F0BFE8548A7528DFE0CF8D1" pageId="325" pageNumber="326" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F0BFE8548A7528DFC88F90D" blockId="325.[151,1436,1441,1970]" pageId="325" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F0BFE8548A7528DFE35FA49" bold="true" box="[151,400,1441,1466]" pageId="325" pageNumber="326">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F0BFE854AA8528DFD56FA49" box="[664,755,1441,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="325" pageNumber="326" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible brown and partly testaceous; antenna brown; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs brown, except tarsi partly testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 6:5:10:8:7:8:7:7:7:7. Head dull, granulated and reticulate rugose; frontal line absent; occipital carina absent; temple absent; POL = 6; OL = 2; OOL = 3; greatest diameter of posterior ocelli longer than OL (3:2). Palpal formula 6/3. Scutum dull, granulated. Notauli complete, posteriorly separated; minimum distance between notauli shorter than POL (2.5:6). Scutellum granulated and punctate. Metanotum shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Propodeum dull, reticulate rugose, with two large reticulate areolae on sides of dorsal region. Forewing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein slightly longer than proximal part (14:13). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F0BFE854B0F51EDFC15F929" box="[831,944,1729,1753]" captionStart="PLATE 95" captionStartId="326.[151,233,1816,1839]" captionTargetBox="[232,1367,206,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-86@326.[188,1398,195,1795]" captionTargetPageId="326" captionText="PLATE 95. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Pronotum in lateral view, holotype. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Neodryinus javanus from Malaya (from Olmi 1984). B. N. karaentensis, holotype (from Olmi 2011a). C, D. N. leptopus (from Olmi 1984). E. N. lineatus (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.21 mm for B, 1.19 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D and E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278708/files/figure.png" pageId="325" pageNumber="326">Plate 95B</figureCitation>
) with proximal dorsal process longer than basivolsella and with serrate distal apex. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F0BFE8548F75025FE0CF8D1" blockId="325.[151,1436,1441,1970]" box="[199,425,1801,1825]" pageId="325" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F0BFE8548F75025FE80F8D1" bold="true" box="[199,293,1801,1825]" pageId="325" pageNumber="326">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
